Connect to remote systems via SSH and forward discovered ports to localhost

Usage: port-linker [OPTIONS] [HOST]

Arguments:
  [HOST]  Remote host in format `[user@]host` [default: josiah@avocado]

Options:
  -p, --ports <PORTS>                  Only forward specific ports (comma-separated)
  -x, --exclude <EXCLUDE>              Exclude specific ports (comma-separated), in addition to defaults
      --no-default-excludes            Don't apply default port exclusions (22, 53, etc.)
      --auto-kill                      Automatically kill conflicting local processes
      --no-notifications               Disable desktop notifications
      --no-sound                       Disable notification sounds
      --log-level <LOG_LEVEL>          Log level (trace, debug, info, warn, error) [default: info]
      --scan-interval <SCAN_INTERVAL>  Port scan interval in seconds [default: 3]
  -i, --identity <IDENTITY_FILE>       Path to SSH identity file
  -P, --port <SSH_PORT>                SSH port [default: 22]
  -h, --help                           Print help
  -V, --version                        Print version
